info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 09 at 8:10PM EST until January 12 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Indianapolis
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Indianapolis IN has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Indiana... East Fork White River at Seymour. .Rainfall this past Saturday night of 1.00 to 1.40 inches over southeastern central Indiana has risen the East Fork of the White River into flood. Flooding is expected to continue through midday Tuesday. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH LATE TUESDAY NIGHT... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...East Fork White River at Seymour. * WHEN...Until early Wednesday morning. * IMPACTS...At 13.5 feet, Lowland flood continues. Jackson County Road 700 E begins to flood. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 6:45 PM EST Sunday the stage was 11.5 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage late this evening to a crest of 13.1 feet early tomorrow afternoon. It will then fall below flood stage early Tuesday afternoon. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov/ind. The next statement should be issued by noon Monday.
